Plug and Play & Wide Compatibility Equipped with 2-in-1 Windows and Mac OS layouts along with a 2-in-1 USB & Type C receiver, the mouse and keyboard combo is a perfect choice for laptops, desktops, PC, Chormebook, MacBook Pro, MacBook air, etc. No need to any drive, take receiver out and plug it into your computer, then start to use. 15 Hot Keys & Fn Lock 15 hotkeys are added for instant access to media controls, copy, paste, save, opening browsers and screen turn off, improving your work efficiency and more convenient to use. Energy Saving On/off switch and automatic sleep mode (after 8mins of inactivity) designs make them keep low power consumption and last long battery life. Comfortable Use Smooth matte surface, lightweight and skin-friendly designs can provide great hand-feeling and keep comfort even working for a long time. Ergonomic Design This wireless keyboard and mouse are designed with ergonomic height, which helps to ease the strain on your wrists and the muscles in arm. Protective Cover The seenda keyboard comes with a silicone cover gift to enhance typing experience, also prevent accidental splashes of water, coffee, dust etc.

1. How many batteries needed? The wireless keyboard works 1 AAA battery, the mouse uses 1 AA battery, and the batteries are not included. 2. What device system needed? This black keyboard and mouse is compatible with Windows XP/Vista/7/8/10+, Mac OS 10.14 or above. 3. Where is the USB A/C receiver？ There is only ONE receiver, stored in the mouse, next to the mouse's battery slot. 4. Why the keyboard can't be switched to OS system? When use the USB C port, please push the USB C receiver fully into your mac. Otherwise, the keyboard and mouse cannot connect to your mac, and you will find that the keyboard cannot turn to OS system. 5. How to switch multimedia or F1-F12 functions? The keyboard is in media functions by default. The F1-F12 functions need to be activated by pressing fn + F1-F12 keys. Or you can activate the fn lock to use the F1-F12 function directly (The fn lock key locates next to the F12 key).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Pretty nice so far
reviews.reviewText: I like this keyboard and mouse so far. The protective cover feels pleasant to the touch and slightly reduces the sound of typing. The setup was quick and easy. I read a review where someone said the USB-C end of the receiver didn't work for them. However, the receiver must be inserted with the arrow side up. The mouse is very responsive and works well on different surfaces. The colors are just as shown and match my Cricut perfectly! Although I had some trouble reconnecting the receiver after disconnecting it for a few hours, I didn't face any issues when I left the receiver connected, even after turning my computer on and off multiple times.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love this set so much I had to buy a second one for my days at the office!! So comfortable, perfect size and gorgeous colors!! The way it feels on the hands... I love it! Mouse runs smooth and keyboard makes a nice sound on each key (not annoying).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Really nice for the price
reviews.reviewText: The mouse is comfortable and the click is very soft. The keyboard is lovely as well. Very impressed by the sleek design and key taps. The mouse alone is worth the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 13, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute and comfortable - but careful with connectivity
reviews.reviewText: I absolutely loved this keyboard and mouse combo - especially for the price. The colors are beautiful and the keys are satisfying to type on. It is a very spacious keyboard and the side number pad makes it easier for me to run codes for my job. My Mac quickly recognized both devices and worked perfectly once the "OS" key was activated. The mouse is also very cute and comfortable. Might seem small to some who use a traditional mouse, but it wasn't an issue for me (I didn't find it small or uncomfortable to use). I also love that the keyboard and mouse use only one battery each.MY ONLY ISSUE SO FAR: the connectivity fails at times. My cat likes to sleep near my laptop (specifically between the laptop and my keyboard/mouse). Every time she lies between the receptor and the devices, the connectivity is slightly interrupted and lags. It seems the reception sensitivity can be affected by barriers directly in the way. If I move my cat out of the way or slightly move the keyboard/mouse to directly face the receptor, the issue goes away... but my cat's favorite spot to nap is right there on my laptop, so it does happen often.
